About the Company
TikTok is a global social media platform that connects people from across the globe. Our platform allows users to share their stories and passions with others, and we believe that this connection is key to building a more compassionate and understanding world. At TikTok, we value diversity, equity, and inclusion, and we strive to create a workplace culture that is welcoming and supportive of all employees.

Our Values
We believe in creating a positive impact on society through our platform, and we strive to do this by celebrating our diverse voices and creating an environment that reflects the many communities we reach. Our values include:
• Innovation: We believe in constantly innovating and pushing the boundaries of what is possible.
• Diversity: We value diversity, equity, and inclusion, and we strive to create a workplace culture that is welcoming and supportive of all employees.
• Compassion: We believe in treating each other with kindness and respect, and we strive to create a workplace culture that is compassionate and understanding.

About the Role
We are seeking a talented individual to join our e-commerce governance team as an algorithm technical manager intern. This role involves developing scientific metrics to measure the success of our e-commerce governance and experience team, as well as working closely with engineers and product managers to drive project execution and iteration by clear problem scoping and design.

Responsibilities
- Develop algorithms to detect various risks that can sabotage platform trust;
- Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify areas for improvement;
- Drive project execution and iteration by clear problem scoping and design;

Requirements
- Currently pursuing a BS/MS degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Economy or other relevant majors;
- Proficient in at least one software programming language, such as SQL/R/Python;
- Good self-driving ability and team cooperation ability, strong sense of responsibility, willingness and ability to challenge oneself and learn new knowledge;

Preferred Qualifications
- Experiences in Hadoop/Spark/Storm and other computing platforms and tools;
- Hands-on experience in open source machine learning frameworks such as pytorch and tensorflow;

Requirements and Qualifications

To be successful in this role, you should have:
• A degree or experience in technical or related fields, such as bioinformatics data preprocessing or quantitative linguistics;
• Excellent command of Python programming language;
• Experience with regular expressions, particularly with right-to-left languages like Hebrew and Arabic;
• Working knowledge of MongoDB, Linux command line environment, and cloud environments (AWS, GCP).

Bonus qualifications include exposure to distance functions and error correction techniques.

